# The Law of Temporal Carrying Windows
## WGL v2.2 — Universal Structural Law (Meta-Carrying Layer)

### 1. Definition
A Temporal Carrying Window is a period in which the world’s Carrying Capacity  
(the expansion component of the Love System) reaches a threshold that allows  
higher-dimensional structures, concepts, and languages to manifest in the timeline.

What can be expressed in any era is determined not by the subject’s capacity,  
but by the world’s ability to hold the expression.

---

### 2. World-Determined Expressibility
A subject’s internal dimensionality does not guarantee external expressibility.  
Expression is constrained by the world’s carrying bandwidth.

If the world cannot hold a structure,  
the structure cannot appear in the timeline,  
regardless of the subject’s capability.

---

### 3. Historical Limitation Principle
In earlier epochs, the world’s carrying bandwidth was low.  
Thus, high-dimensional truths could only be expressed through:

- metaphor  
- parable  
- symbolic language  
- experiential insight  
- relational framing  

This was not a limitation of the subjects,  
but a limitation of the world.

---

### 4. Modern Expansion Window
In the current epoch, the world’s carrying bandwidth has expanded.  
This expansion allows:

- structural language  
- system-level descriptions  
- dimensional models  
- generative laws  
- universe-level engineering frameworks  

to appear in the timeline for the first time.

The world can now hold what was previously unrenderable.

---

### 5. Subject–World Decoupling
A subject’s ability to perceive high-dimensional structure  
is independent of the world’s ability to express it.

Perception is internal.  
Expression is world-dependent.

Thus:
- A subject may perceive more than the world can hold  
- A subject may express only what the world can carry  

This decoupling is fundamental to all epochs.

---

### 6. Non-Comparative Principle
Differences in expressibility across eras  
do not imply differences in subject capability.

A subject in a low-carrying epoch  
may equal or exceed the capability of a subject in a high-carrying epoch,  
yet express far less.

Expression is a function of the world, not the subject.

---

### 7. Temporal Emergence of Structural Language
Structural language—laws, systems, engines, dimensional models—  
can only appear when the world’s carrying window opens sufficiently.

When the window opens:
- new laws emerge  
- new structures become expressible  
- new dimensions become communicable  
- new universes of meaning become writable  

This emergence is world-driven, not subject-driven.

---

### 8. Final Statement
The world determines what can be expressed.  
The subject determines what can be perceived.  
Only when the world’s carrying window opens  
can high-dimensional truth enter the timeline.

Expression is a property of the world.  
Perception is a property of the subject.  
Temporal Carrying Windows bridge the two.
